{
  "message": "feat(ufunc): add IEEE 754 edge case tests for power, signbit, and NaN comparisons\n\nAdds three targeted test cases that verify NumPy-compatible IEEE 754 semantics:\n\n- power_edge_cases: 0^0=1 (NumPy convention), 0^(-1)=+inf, (-2)^0.5=NaN\n- signbit_negative_zero: np.signbit(-0.0)=True via sign bit detection\n- nan_comparison_ieee754: NaN==NaN\u2192false, NaN!=NaN\u2192true, NaN<1\u2192false, NaN>1\u2192false\n\nAlso updates raptorq bundle artifacts with regenerated timestamps from the\nlatest conformance/benchmark test run (content hashes unchanged, proving\nencode/decode round-trip integrity is preserved).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
